<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="407" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
Depicted in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1515/9783111625430-fm" author="Ahl, E" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B9" refString="Ahl, E, 1931b. Amphibia, Anura III, Polypedatidae. In: Hesse R (Ed.) Das Tierreich. Eine Zusammenstellung und Kennzeichnung der rezenten Tierformen. 55. Lieferung. Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co. Berlin und Leipzig, 477 pp. [+ (1-2)]. https://doi.org/10.1515/9783111625430-fm" title="Amphibia, Anura III, Polypedatidae. In: Hesse R (Ed.) Das Tierreich. Eine Zusammenstellung und Kennzeichnung der rezenten Tierformen. 55. Lieferung. Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co. Berlin und Leipzig, 477 pp. [+ (1 - 2)]." url="https://doi.org/10.1515/9783111625430-fm" year="1931 b">Ahl (1931b</bibRefCitation>
: 419, fig. 291). The German botanist, ethnologist and explorer Tessmann travelled to Cameroon in 1904, where he worked until 1905 for the West African plantation company Bibundi as a supervisor on a cocoa plantation. Afterwards he travelled to the Cameroon Hinterland [
<normalizedToken originalValue="‚Hinterland‘">'Hinterland'</normalizedToken>
is a term in the colonial literature, used in various languages; it does not specify a specific geographic region but refers generally to regions being away from the coast or provincial towns] and to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yaoundé">Yaounde</normalizedToken>
and founded his own plantation in the border area between German-Cameroon and Spanish-Guinea. From 1907 to 1909 he was the head of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Lübecker">&quot;Luebecker</normalizedToken>
Pangwe-Expedition&quot; to South Cameroon and Equatorial Guinea and in 1913 he led an expedition to &quot;Neu Kamerun&quot;. During the First World War he fled to Spanish Guinea and was interned by the Spanish on Fernando 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pó">Po</normalizedToken>
[Bioko]. Later, he turned to South America, travelled through Peru, and emigrated to Brazil in 1936, where he settled in the state of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
and got a position at the Museu Paranaense. During his stay in Africa he collected large numbers of zoological, botanical and ethnological objects, most of which were sent to the museums in Berlin and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lübeck">Luebeck</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dinslage, S" journalOrPublisher="Luebecker Beitraege zur Ethnologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="1 - 477" refId="B48" refString="Dinslage, S, Templin, B, 2012. Mein Leben [G. T. Tessmann]. Tagebuch in 12 Baenden. Teil 1, Abschnitt I-II. Luebecker Beitraege zur Ethnologie 2: 1 - 477" title="Mein Leben [G. T. Tessmann]. Tagebuch in 12 Baenden. Teil 1, Abschnitt I-II." volume="2" year="2012">Dinslage and Templin 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dinslage, S" journalOrPublisher="Luebecker Beitraege zur Ethnologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="1 - 544" refId="B47" refString="Dinslage, S, 2015. Mein Leben [G. T. Tessmann]. Tagebuch in 12 Baenden. Teil 3, Abschnitt IV-V. Luebecker Beitraege zur Ethnologie 4: 1 - 544" title="Mein Leben [G. T. Tessmann]. Tagebuch in 12 Baenden. Teil 3, Abschnitt IV-V." volume="4" year="2015">Dinslage 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Templin, B" journalOrPublisher="Luebecker Beitraege zur Ethnologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="1 - 304" refId="B214" refString="Templin, B, 2015. Mein Leben [G. T. Tessmann]. Tagebuch in 12 Baenden. Teil 2, Abschnitt III. Luebecker Beitraege zur Ethnologie 3: 1 - 304" title="Mein Leben [G. T. Tessmann]. Tagebuch in 12 Baenden. Teil 2, Abschnitt III." volume="3" year="2015">Templin 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" class="Reptilia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperolius acuticephalus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acuticephalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Hyperolius acuticephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be conspecific with either 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. igbettensis" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="igbettensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. igbettensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schiøtz">Schiotz</normalizedToken>
, 1963 or 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. adsperus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adsperus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. adsperus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Peters, 1877. Type locality and shape of head better fit 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. igebettensis" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="igebettensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. igebettensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fide 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3620.3.1" author="Channing, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="301 - 350" refId="B35" refString="Channing, A, Hillers, A, Loetters, S, Roedel, M-O, Schick, S, Conradie, W, Roedder, D, Mercurio, V, Wagner, P, Dehling, JM, Du Preez, LH, Kielgast, J, Burger, M, 2013. Taxonomy of the super-cryptic Hyperolius nasutus group of long reed frogs of Africa (Anura: Hyperoliidae), with descriptions of six new species. Zootaxa 3620 (3): 301 - 350, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3620.3.1" title="Taxonomy of the super-cryptic Hyperolius nasutus group of long reed frogs of Africa (Anura: Hyperoliidae), with descriptions of six new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3620.3.1" volume="3620" year="2013">Channing et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
); concerning webbing of feet 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. acuticephalus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acuticephalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. acuticephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is intermediate between 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. igbettensis" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="igbettensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. igbettensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. adspersus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adspersus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. adspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fide 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3620.3.1" author="Channing, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="301 - 350" refId="B35" refString="Channing, A, Hillers, A, Loetters, S, Roedel, M-O, Schick, S, Conradie, W, Roedder, D, Mercurio, V, Wagner, P, Dehling, JM, Du Preez, LH, Kielgast, J, Burger, M, 2013. Taxonomy of the super-cryptic Hyperolius nasutus group of long reed frogs of Africa (Anura: Hyperoliidae), with descriptions of six new species. Zootaxa 3620 (3): 301 - 350, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3620.3.1" title="Taxonomy of the super-cryptic Hyperolius nasutus group of long reed frogs of Africa (Anura: Hyperoliidae), with descriptions of six new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3620.3.1" volume="3620" year="2013">Channing et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
); the ratio of head width/snout-vent length speaks in favor of 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. adspersus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adspersus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. adspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fide 
<bibRefCitation author="Amiet, J-L" journalOrPublisher="La Nef des Livres, Saint-Nazaire, France" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B11" refString="Amiet, J-L, 2012. Les Rainettes du Cameroun (Amphibiens Anoures). La Nef des Livres, Saint-Nazaire, France" title="Les Rainettes du Cameroun (Amphibiens Anoures)." year="2012">Amiet 2012</bibRefCitation>
); and the ratio of head length/head width points again to 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. igbettensis" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="igbettensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. igbettensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fide 
<bibRefCitation author="Amiet, J-L" journalOrPublisher="La Nef des Livres, Saint-Nazaire, France" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B11" refString="Amiet, J-L, 2012. Les Rainettes du Cameroun (Amphibiens Anoures). La Nef des Livres, Saint-Nazaire, France" title="Les Rainettes du Cameroun (Amphibiens Anoures)." year="2012">Amiet 2012</bibRefCitation>
); finally the value for the length of the snout/head width surpasses both 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. igebettensis" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="igebettensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. igebettensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. adspersus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adspersus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. adspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
